{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, a significant percentage of Tobacco800 are consecutively numbered multi-page business documents, making it a valuable test for various content-based document image retrieval approaches.",
    "The second collection, instead, annotates a subsection of the RVL-CDIP invoices class for table detection and layout analysis, gathering some important information such as sender, receiver, and total amount.Over several years, important competitions have been organized at the ICDAR conferences releasing benchmarks for TD and TSR that, nowadays, are still used to compare different methods.",
    "The most important ones to be cited are ICDAR 2013 [77] and ICDAR 2019 [78].",
    "The first collection counts 156 tables crawled from two government sources site:europa.eu and site:*.gov.",
    "The organizers searched for tables keeping two pages after and before them, giving space for false positive detection."
  ]
}